description:
In src/ui/InGameMenu.ts confirmReset() method (~line 1274):

Currently after resetGame() and quickSave(), the method calls this.hide() and then switchScene('main-menu'). 

Change: Remove the switchScene('main-menu') call. Just hide the menu so the player stays in the current scene (apartment). The state is already reset in memory and saved to localStorage.

The method currently looks like:
  this.game.store.getState().resetGame();
  await this.game.saveManager.quickSave();
  this.hide();
  await this.game.switchScene('main-menu');  // REMOVE THIS LINE

After the change it should just:
  this.game.store.getState().resetGame();
  await this.game.saveManager.quickSave();
  this.hide();
